54
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:13,970
and seeing Christ minister to the lost around the world.

55
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,700
Most of us have had times.

56
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:23,020
We've sensed that God has planted a dream within us.

57
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:27,700
And yet, most of us can identify with having dreams

58
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:29,820
that were never realized.

59
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:32,980
Ideas that never came to fruition.

60
00:04:34,530 --> 00:04:37,350
And as a result, some of us have become resistant

61
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:40,630
to the idea of allowing God

62
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:43,110
the luxury of planting a dream

63
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:44,510
within our minds again.

64
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:47,210
We're not going to go there again.

65
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,480
We don't want to be set up

66
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,720
for another disappointment.

67
00:04:54,430 --> 00:04:55,430
But what if God,

68
00:04:55,930 --> 00:04:58,570
what if God wants to resurrect

69
00:04:58,570 --> 00:05:00,190
our past dreams

70
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:02,810
