73
00:05:10,730 --> 00:05:14,470
but it's also possible to dream new dreams.

74
00:05:15,210 --> 00:05:19,170
What keeps you back from dreaming God-sized dreams

75
00:05:19,170 --> 00:05:22,450
for your life, for your church, for your community?

76
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:30,080
What holds you back from taking big steps with God?

77
00:05:32,370 --> 00:05:34,910
What shrinks your spirit from believing

78
00:05:34,910 --> 00:05:38,530
that God can do big things through you?

79
00:05:42,710 --> 00:05:44,710
Sometimes there's barriers in our lives

80
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:46,830
to becoming all that God wants us to be,

81
00:05:46,970 --> 00:05:54,090
They can arise from fear, insecurity, doubt, disappointment.

82
00:05:55,710 --> 00:05:57,810
Do any of those have a hold on you?

83
00:06:00,380 --> 00:06:04,960
Do you think small because you've been burned in the past?

84
00:06:06,610 --> 00:06:12,490
Do you dream small because you're afraid of failure or of success?

85
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:18,600
Here's a question that rattles around and disturbs my soul.

86
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:24,960
If you had no fear of failure, what would you attempt for God?

87
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:30,080
If you had no fear that what you would step out and do,

88
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:34,480
if there's no fear of failure, what would you attempt for God?

89
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,130
That's a disturbing question, isn't it?

90
00:06:40,540 --> 00:06:44,900
What is it you want to lay at the Master's feet when your life is over?

91
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:51,240
If you had no fear of failure, what would you attempt for God?

92
00:06:54,890 --> 00:06:57,910
This summer, these next eight weeks, we're going to unpack this idea

93
00:06:57,910 --> 00:06:59,330
of daring to dream again.

94
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:03,460
I believe that looking at God's word

95
00:07:03,460 --> 00:07:05,120
and having it minister to our souls,

96
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,240
we're going to get insight

97
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,940
on how to break through some barriers

98
00:07:07,940 --> 00:07:09,360
that can hold us back

99
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,420
from being all that God wants us to be.

100
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:13,580
Many of us live under a glass ceiling.

101
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,000
We don't know it's there,

102
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:16,360
but it holds us back

103
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:19,340
from being all that He wants us to be.

104
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,320
To dream and to step out

105
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:23,560
and to believe and to take bold steps for God,

106
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,200
we hold back.

107
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:28,220
And I want us to break glass this summer

108
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:30,770
and go to new places with God.

109
00:07:32,530 --> 00:07:34,690
I'm indebted to the insight of Dr. David Maines

110
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:35,970
and Dr. Bill Shereos

111
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:38,870
as they shared some insight that's helped me

112
00:07:38,870 --> 00:07:40,390
unpack these ideas.

113
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:47,160
A painful past, friends, can inhibit our dreams.

114
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:50,630
Perhaps some of you are sitting there

115
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:52,830
